Package it.emarolab.owloop.descriptor.utility.conceptDescriptor

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DefinitionConceptDesc
    This is an example of a 'compound' Concept Descriptor that implements 4 ClassExpressions (aka ConceptExpression): ConceptExpression.Equivalent: to describe that a Class is equivalent to another Class. ConceptExpression.Disjoint: to describe that a Class is disjoint to another Class. ConceptExpression.Instance: to describe an Individual of a Class. ConceptExpression.Definition: to describe the definition of a Class.. See FullConceptDescriptor for an example of a 'compound' Concept Descriptor that implements all ClassExpressions (aka ConceptExpression).
    FullConceptDescriptor
    This is an example of a 'compound' Concept Descriptor as it implements more than one ClassExpression (aka ConceptExpression).
    HierarchicalConceptDesc
    This is an example of a 'compound' Concept Descriptor that implements 2 ClassExpressions (aka ConceptExpression): ConceptExpression.Sub: to describe that a Class subsumes another Class. ConceptExpression.Super: to describe that a Class is a super-class of another Class. See FullConceptDescriptor for an example of a 'compound' Concept Descriptor that implements all ClassExpressions (aka ConceptExpression).
    InstanceConceptDesc
    This is an example of a 'compound' Concept Descriptor that implements 1 ClassExpressions (aka ConceptExpression): ConceptExpression.Instance: to describe an Individual of a Class. See FullConceptDescriptor for an example of a 'compound' Concept Descriptor that implements all ClassExpressions (aka ConceptExpression).
